title: Billings Central soccer playoff matches set
text:

After the win, Ndedi flew to Polson where he coached the Rams boys to a victory as well. Billings Central soccer playoff matches set Updated Buy Now BOB ZELLAR/Gazette Staff 
Billings Central soccer coach Didier Ndedi directs his girls team to a 5-1 win over Corvallis in the Class A quarterfinals Saturday. After the win, Ndedi flew to Polson where he coached the Rams boys to a victory as well. 
The Billings Central boys and girls soccer teams are hosting State A semifinal soccer games Saturday. 
The Rams girls (10-0-1) will play Whitefish (10-3-1) at 11 a.m. The Central boys (9-2-0) will go up against Corvallis (12-1-0) at 1 p.m. Both games are at Wendy's Field on the campus of Rocky Mountain College. 
Ticket prices are $7 for adults and $6 for students. Regular-season passes won't be accepted. Tags
